{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "09", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "29", "S": "27"}}, "news": [{"title": "SBI pitches for review of affordable home definition, cites jump in average loan size", "para": "SBI Chairman C S Setty has urged the government to redefine affordable housing, citing a significant rise in the average home loan size to Rs 51 lakh from Rs 35-40 lakh two years ago. He stated that increasing housing costs necessitate a review of what constitutes an affordable home, impacting policy incentives for lenders.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/sbi-calls-for-review-of-affordable-housing-definition-amid-rising-loan-sizes/130970341?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-54112/130970341.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "RBI imposes penalties on YES Bank, Hinduja Housing Finance", "para": "The Reserve Bank of India has levied a Rs 31.80 lakh penalty on YES Bank for failing to implement a system for using KYC Identifiers for customer relationships. This action follows a supervisory inspection of the bank's financial position as of March 31, 2025. Additionally, Hinduja Housing Finance Ltd was fined Rs 1.8 lakh for governance non-compliance.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/housing-finance/rbi-fines-yes-bank-and-hinduja-housing-finance-for-compliance-violations/130970322?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-86574/130970322.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "housing-finance"}, {"title": "Uttar Pradesh reduces development and building permit fee in Ghaziabad", "para": "The Uttar Pradesh government has slightly reduced development and building permit fees in districts like Ghaziabad. This follows a substantial increase earlier this year. Ghaziabad still holds the highest development fee in the state. The government aims to leverage Ghaziabad's growth potential for infrastructure development.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/uttar-pradesh-cuts-development-and-building-permit-fees-in-ghaziabad/130970283?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-206936/130970283.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}